<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
   <title> Try It Yourself </title>
   <style type="text/css">
      span:only-of-type {
         background: #78969D;
         color: #f8f9f9;
      }
   </style>
</head>
<body>
   <p> The <b>:only-of-type</b> CSS pseudo-class represents an element that has no siblings of the same type. </p>
   
   <h3> Example: </h3>
   <p> In this example, the <b>&lt;span&gt;</b> element is only selected if it is the only <b>&lt;span&gt;</b> element inside its parent. </p>
   
   <div>
      <em> Hello World! I love Codeliber! </em>
      <span> I am the only <b>span</b> element inside this <b>div</b> element. </span>
   </div>
   
   <div>
      <i> Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet. </i>
      <span> I am NOT THE ONLY <b>span</b> element inside this <b>div</b> element. </span>
      <span> I am NOT THE ONLY <b>span</b> element inside this <b>div</b> element. </span>
   </div>
</body>
</html>